	<item>
		<title>Software and tools</title>
		<link>/blog/post1/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 19 Aug 2023 13:21:54 +0100</pubDate>
		
		<guid>/blog/post1/</guid>
		<description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: center; margin-bottom:  20px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  20px; font-size: 25px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
    What i use: 
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;Presented below are a selection of the software and tools that I use showcasing a range of essential utilities that play a crucial role in my computing experience.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: center; margin-bottom:  5px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  5px; font-size: 25px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
    Criteria
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;My software choices are defined by the principles of extensibility, minimalism, and a strong commitment to the Unix
philosophy, These principles guide me to tools that offer efficiency, customization, and seamless integration. The
&lt;code&gt;suckless&lt;/code&gt; software serves as a prime example, embodying these values and creating a cohesive and effective digital
ecosystem
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
    Distro
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Arch&lt;/code&gt; is my go-to choice due to its supportive community, the wide array of software available through the AUR, and
the invaluable resource that is the Arch Wiki
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
    WM
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Dwm&lt;/code&gt; for its lightweight,adaptable and extensible nature
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
    Terminal
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;St&lt;/code&gt; known to be an extremely minimal terminal emulator.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
     Net Browsing
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Firefox&lt;/code&gt; &lt;em&gt;with tweaked&lt;/em&gt; &lt;code&gt;Arkenfox&lt;/code&gt; &lt;em&gt;User.js&lt;/em&gt;: for a privacy-focused and secure browsing experience of the modern web&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;ytfzf&lt;/code&gt;: for consuming youtube without the bloat&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Searx&lt;/code&gt;: For private and secure web searches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
     File Manager
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Lf&lt;/code&gt;, a terminal file manager written in Go, heavily inspired by &lt;code&gt;ranger&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
     RSS Reader
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;newsboat&lt;/code&gt;, an efficient RSS reader to replace social media and  keep track of the latest updates from your chosen sources
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
     Image viewing
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Nsxiv&lt;/code&gt;, a maintained fork of sxiv, offers high scriptability
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
     Document Creation
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;LaTex&lt;/code&gt;, a powerful typesetting system renowned for its ability to create visually appealing and professionally formatted
documents
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
     Pdf Viewer
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Zathura&lt;/code&gt;,pdf viewer with vim bindings
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
     Presentations
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Sent&lt;/code&gt;, a simple presentation tool that elegantly converts plain text and images into slides
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
     Text Editor
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Vim&lt;/code&gt;, basicly &lt;code&gt;neovim&lt;/code&gt; text editor
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
    Shell
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:20px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 50px&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Zsh&lt;/code&gt;, Command-Line Utilities with Extra Addons
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
    Scripting
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;dmenu&lt;/code&gt;: A dynamic menu&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;smenu&lt;/code&gt;: menu selection with a more intuitive and interactive interface.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;fzf&lt;/code&gt;: A versatile fuzzy finder&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;herbe&lt;/code&gt;: A minimalist notification daemon for unobtrusive alerts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;xclip&lt;/code&gt;: A clipboard utility for easy copying and pasting of text.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;entr&lt;/code&gt;: A tool that automates tasks based on file changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;wjt&lt;/code&gt;: A slider widget, allowing easy selection within a range&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;nq&lt;/code&gt; : queue utilitie&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;pv&lt;/code&gt; : Pipe Viewer for monitoring the progress&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;fzy&lt;/code&gt;: simple fuzzy text selector&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  1px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  1px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #953d1d;&#34;&gt;
    Other Useful Tools
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; justify-content: left; align-items: left; &#34;&gt; 

&lt;p style=&#34; font-size:100px; margin-top:0.1px; 
    margin-left: 30px&#34;&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;xdg-ninja&lt;/code&gt;: to clean up your $HOME directory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;brightnessctl&lt;/code&gt;: A handy tool for adjusting screen brightness levels from the command line.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;arch-wiki-man&lt;/code&gt;: get the arch wiki as man pages offline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;xbanish&lt;/code&gt; : Hide the cursor while typing.&lt;/li&gt;
