&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: center; margin-bottom:  20px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  20px; font-size: 30px; font-weight: bold; color: #be4d25;&#34;&gt;
    Using the sent Presentation Tool
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  20px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  20px; font-size: 25px; font-weight: bold; color: #be4d25;&#34;&gt;
    What is sent?
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt; is a simple, lightweight, and command-line-based presentation tool. It allows you to create slideshows by using plain text files, making it easy to focus on the content of your presentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  20px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  20px; font-size: 25px; font-weight: bold; color: #be4d25;&#34;&gt;
    Why Use sent?
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simplicity:&lt;/strong&gt; Creating slides is as easy as writing paragraphs in a text file.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimal Distraction:&lt;/strong&gt; No need to worry about design, animations, or complex slide transitions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lightweight:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt; is lightweight and efficient, making it a great choice for quick presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  20px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  20px; font-size: 25px; font-weight: bold; color: #be4d25;&#34;&gt;
    Installation
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To install &lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt; , you can use the following command:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;style&gt;
  .vim-code-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .vim-code {
    background-color: #1c1c1c;
    color: #b9b9b9;
    font-family: &#34;Courier New&#34;, monospace;
    padding: 5px;
    border: 2px solid #4e4e4e;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
    margin: 20px auto;
    max-width: calc(100% + 40px);  
  }
&lt;/style&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;vim-code-container&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;vim-code&#34; style=&#34;line-height: 1; font-size:15px;&#34;&gt;
    
git clone https://git.suckless.org/sent
cd sent
sudo make clean install

  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before using &lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt;, make sure you have the required dependencies installed, which are &lt;code&gt;libx11&lt;/code&gt;,&lt;code&gt;libxft&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;farbfeld&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;

&lt;style&gt;
  .vim-code-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .vim-code {
    background-color: #1c1c1c;
    color: #b9b9b9;
    font-family: &#34;Courier New&#34;, monospace;
    padding: 5px;
    border: 2px solid #4e4e4e;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
    margin: 20px auto;
    max-width: calc(100% + 40px);  
  }
&lt;/style&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;vim-code-container&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;vim-code&#34; style=&#34;line-height: 0.5; font-size:20px;&#34;&gt;
    
sudo pacman -S libx11 libxft

  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;code&gt;farbfeld&lt;/code&gt; for the images to render


&lt;style&gt;
  .vim-code-container {
    display: flex;
