&lt;div class=&#34;vim-code-container&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;vim-code&#34; style=&#34;line-height: 1; font-size:15px;&#34;&gt;
    
git clone https://git.suckless.org/farbfeld
cd farbfeld
sudo make clean install

  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: left; margin-bottom:  20px;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  20px; font-size: 25px; font-weight: bold; color: #be4d25;&#34;&gt;
    How to Use sent
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;to-create-and-run-a-presentation-using-sent&#34;&gt;To create and run a presentation using &lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;in a text file Each slide is separated by a blank line&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use lines starting with &lt;code&gt;#&lt;/code&gt; for comments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;@FILENAME&lt;/code&gt; to add an image slide, e.g., &lt;code&gt;@slide.png&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;\&lt;/code&gt;  for empty slides&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To run the presentation, use the following command:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;style&gt;
  .vim-code-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .vim-code {
    background-color: #1c1c1c;
    color: #b9b9b9;
