  &lt;h1 style=&#34; margin-bottom:  20px; font-size: 25px; font-weight: bold; color: #be4d25;&#34;&gt;
    Patching
  &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patching is a method used to modify or extend software without altering the original source code. In the context of
&lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt;, patching allows you to customize its behavior, add new features, or fix issues while still being able to update
the software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Download the Patch&lt;/strong&gt; : &lt;a href=&#34;https://tools.suckless.org/sent/patches&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;suckless sent patches&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply the Patch&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open a terminal and navigate to the directory where the &lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt; source code is located. Apply the patch using the
&lt;code&gt;patch&lt;/code&gt; command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;style&gt;
  .vim-code-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .vim-code {
    background-color: #1c1c1c;
    color: #b9b9b9;
    font-family: &#34;Courier New&#34;, monospace;
    padding: 5px;
    border: 2px solid #4e4e4e;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
    margin: 20px auto;
    max-width: calc(100% + 40px);  
  }
&lt;/style&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;vim-code-container&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;vim-code&#34; style=&#34;line-height: 1; font-size:17px;&#34;&gt;
    
patch -i [path_to_patch_file]
sudo cp config.def.h config.h

  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This command applies the changes specified in the patch file to the &lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt; source code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compile &lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recompile the modified &lt;code&gt;sent&lt;/code&gt; source code to generate the patched executable:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;style&gt;
  .vim-code-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .vim-code {
